      • ordered_iterate

        public int[][] ordered_iterate​(int axis)
        For example assume I have tensor 1 2 3 4 5 6 The iteration over defined inside iterator would take this order: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 - primarily iterating over the last axis (cols). The cols axis changes the most. What if I wanted to iterate over the rows axis instead? In order 1, 4, 2, 5, 3, 6? ordered_iterate implements this functionality. Rows are axis = 0, so ordered_iterate(0) would do the job.
        Parameters:
        axis - The axis to iterate over
        Returns:
        an ArrayList of indices in order where the given axis changes the most
